  <description>
    <line>PULSE EFFECT DEMONSTRATION SEQUENCE</line>
    <line>This sample demonstrates the pulse effect using a pink noise background.</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>HOW PULSE WORKS:</line>
    <line>The "pulse" effect creates a rhythmic pulsing sensation by modulating the amplitude of the</line>
    <line>background sound chosen by the user.</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>PULSE PARAMETERS:</line>
    <line>- rate: pulse frequency (e.g. 10Hz = 10 pulses per second)</line>
    <line>- intensity: depth of amplitude modulation (e.g. 50 = moderate pulsing)</line>
    <line>- amplitude: amplitude of the background sound (e.g. 50% amplitude)</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>The pulse effect works by modulating the amplitude of the background sound in a rhythmic pattern,</line>
    <line>creating a sensation of isochronic pulses. The sound "pulses" evenly, ideal for focus and relaxation.</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>TEMPORAL SEQUENCE BREAKDOWN:</line>
    <line>00:00-00:15: Fade in from silence</line>
    <line>00:15-02:00: Pulse effect with moderate rate (10Hz) and intensity (50).</line>
    <line>03:30-04:30: Pulse effect with slower rate (5Hz) and lower intensity (35).</line>
    <line>05:30-07:00: From ramp back to moderate rate (10Hz) and intensity (50).</line>
    <line>09:30-10:00: Fade out to silence</line>
    <line>10:00+: End of sequence</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>Monaural tone added to enhance the experience with pulse effect.</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>USAGE TIP:</line>
    <line>Use headphones to best experience the pulse effect.</line>
    <line>The pulse effect is ideal for relaxation and can help with focus and concentration.</line>
    <line></line>
    <line>For a more subtle effect, use lower Intensity values; higher values make the</line>
    <line>pulsating sensation stronger. You can also experiment with different waveforms for</line>
    <line>the background pulse to make the effect more pronounced or more gentle, according</line>
    <line>to your preference.</line>
  </description>
